<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="33" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,351,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named in honor of its collector, the late Prof. Yang Chi-kun, to commemorate his outstanding contribution to the Chinese insect taxonomy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,326,229,255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[665,1017,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bicaubittacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="appendiculatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[665,1017,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Bicaubittacus appendiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1025,1161,229,255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1025,1161,229,255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in appearance, but can be separated from the latter by the dorsal margin of epandrial appendage extending caudo-mesad into a long sabre-shaped lobe with a row of black spines; gonostylus long, apex slender and rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,344,370]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Description.</emphasis>
Body 
<quantity box="[426,507,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
long. Wingspan 
<quantity box="[704,790,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="36.0">36 mm</quantity>
. Forewing 
<quantity box="[918,1022,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.76" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="17.6">17.6 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1094,1184,345,371]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
wide. Hindwing 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.51" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="15.1">15.1 mm</quantity>
long, 3.0 mm wide. Vertex, frons, rostrum, maxillary palps, and labial palps yellowish brown. Antennae filiform, yellowish brown, about 
<quantity box="[552,644,422,448]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
long; flagellum ciliated, with about 
<number box="[1086,1116,422,448]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" value="19.0">19</number>
flagellomeres. Compound eyes black; ocellar triangle black, slightly protuberant.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Pronotum unevenly dark brown; two long, black setae along the anterior margin. Anterior half of mesonotum unevenly blackish brown laterally, light brown medially; the remaining part and metanotum pale brown. Pleura and legs yellowish brown; femora and tibiae dark at apices; fourth tarsomere with a spine on each side.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,758]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
Wings (
<figureCitation box="[288,358,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1776,1800]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,815,1751]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,815,1751]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., holotype male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190077/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[343,358,654,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) unspotted, with yellowish tint; pterostigma prominent; pale thyridium at FM. On forewing Pcv 
<number box="[202,220,693,719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" value="2.0">2</number>
; Av absent; Cuv ending at the level of FM; 
<number box="[729,739,693,719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
A terminating far before FM; Sc ending near FRs; Scv near FRs. Hindwing similar to forewing, but Sc ending far before FRs; Scv near ORs.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,765,1776,1800]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190077/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" targetBox="[151,1434,815,1751]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,765,1776,1800]" box="[151,765,1776,1800]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1776,1800]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[288,500,1777,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bicaubittacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[288,500,1777,1800]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Bicaubittacus yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[507,592,1776,1800]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[507,592,1776,1800]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype male.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" targetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,991,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,285,991,1015]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[292,511,992,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bicaubittacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[292,511,992,1015]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">Bicaubittacus yangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[519,607,991,1015]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[519,607,991,1015]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male genitalia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[791,818,991,1015]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">A.</emphasis>
Genitalia, lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1085,1110,991,1015]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">B.</emphasis>
Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,559,1023,1047]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">C.</emphasis>
Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1293,1320,1023,1047]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">D.</emphasis>
Epandrial appendages, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1120,1648]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Abdomen of male with terga II–VIII yellowish brown; each tergum with a narrow black antecosta; posterior margin of terga VI–VIII deeply emarginated, V-shaped; posterior angles of terga VI–VII blackish brown. Epandrial appendages yellowish brown, very large and highly modified; in dorsal aspect, bases fused narrowly, extending caudad into a small median process; basal 
<number box="[887,902,1236,1262]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[911,924,1236,1262]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="3.0">3</number>
curved mesad, extending caudo-mesad into two small processes (
<figureCitation box="[415,491,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,257,991,1015]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[203,1384,197,966]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Genitalia, lateral view; B. Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; C. Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; D. Epandrial appendages, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[474,491,1274,1300]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D), and long sabre-shaped lobe with a row of black spines extending ventrocaudally from the inner side of the epandrial appendages (
<figureCitation box="[867,942,1313,1339]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,257,991,1015]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[203,1384,197,966]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Genitalia, lateral view; B. Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; C. Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; D. Epandrial appendages, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[925,942,1313,1339]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A); long, broad process directed ventrad subbasally from ventral margin of the epandrial appendages (
<figureCitation box="[901,979,1352,1378]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,257,991,1015]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[203,1384,197,966]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Genitalia, lateral view; B. Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; C. Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; D. Epandrial appendages, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Figs 
<number box="[963,979,1352,1378]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B); epandrial appendages abruptly narrowed for there distal third into an apical prolongation (
<figureCitation box="[862,935,1390,1416]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,257,991,1015]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[203,1384,197,966]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Genitalia, lateral view; B. Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; C. Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; D. Epandrial appendages, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[919,935,1390,1416]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Gonocoxites elongated apically into a pair of slender, weakly sclerotized, setiferous prolongations with sparse, long, black setae along the distal part; tapering toward apex (
<figureCitation box="[485,558,1468,1494]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,257,991,1015]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[203,1384,197,966]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Genitalia, lateral view; B. Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; C. Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; D. Epandrial appendages, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[542,558,1468,1494]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Gonostylus long and slender, with rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[1202,1280,1468,1494]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,257,991,1015]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[203,1384,197,966]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Genitalia, lateral view; B. Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; C. Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; D. Epandrial appendages, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Figs 
<number box="[1264,1280,1468,1494]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A, C). Upper branch of proctiger long, with a dorsal subapical tuft of hairs; apex emarginated into two unequal processes, roughly L-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[374,444,1545,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,257,991,1015]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[203,1384,197,966]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Genitalia, lateral view; B. Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; C. Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; D. Epandrial appendages, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[428,444,1545,1571]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Aedeagus very small, with scoop-like penunci at each side of its base; penisfilum short and coiled (
<figureCitation box="[354,425,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,257,991,1015]" captionTargetBox="[213,1375,199,963]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[203,1384,197,966]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bicaubittacus yangi sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Genitalia, lateral view; B. Ventro-basal process of right epandrial appendage, inner view; C. Left gonostylus and part of cercus and gonocoxite, lateral view; D. Epandrial appendages, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190078/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[409,425,1584,1610]" pageId="7" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
